article.headline: South Alabama 73, New Mexico State 64
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Mario Jointer scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds to help lead South Alabama to a 73-64 victory over New Mexico State on Saturday night. Jointer made 5-of-14 shots, four of them 3-pointers, for South Alabama, which shot 8-of-21 from behind the arc. Richard Law added 15 points and Stephen Cowherd, who was perfect in 10 free throw attempts, added 14. Brandon Gordon scored 10 points as the Jaguars (4-11, 1-3 Sun Belt Conference) held the Aggies winless in the league. Duane John shot 5-of-11 from the field, including three 3-pointers, to lead New Mexico State (4-12, 0-3) with a game-high 24 points. Josh Jenkins added 16 points and Mike Mitchell had 12. The Jaguars shot 21-of-28 from the foul line, and hit 40 percent of their shots overall.
